{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/eng/frontend/19-09-18/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Before building a project yourself, let's examine someone else's project directory structure to get a sense of how to organize directories. In my case, I referenced the directory structure of a friend who had studied React before me. Since directory structures vary from person to person, please use this only as a reference.</p>\n<h3 id=\"react-project\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#react-project\" aria-label=\"react project permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>React Project</h3>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 594px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/348127727b5a5277fa405b6079e50c88/5fd3e/19-09-18-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 43.68421052631579%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/348127727b5a5277fa405b6079e50c88/15813/19-09-18-1.webp 190w,\n/static/348127727b5a5277fa405b6079e50c88/1cdb2/19-09-18-1.webp 380w,\n/static/348127727b5a5277fa405b6079e50c88/bc223/19-09-18-1.webp 594w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/348127727b5a5277fa405b6079e50c88/a2d4f/19-09-18-1.png 190w,\n/static/348127727b5a5277fa405b6079e50c88/3f520/19-09-18-1.png 380w,\n/static/348127727b5a5277fa405b6079e50c88/5fd3e/19-09-18-1.png 594w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 594px) 100vw, 594px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/348127727b5a5277fa405b6079e50c88/5fd3e/19-09-18-1.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>build</strong>: The React deployment folder generated by the <code class=\"language-text\">npm run build</code> command</li>\n<li><strong>node_modules</strong>: The folder where modules installed via <code class=\"language-text\">npm install</code> are located</li>\n<li><strong>public</strong>: The folder where static assets are located</li>\n<li><strong>src</strong>: The folder containing components / containers / pages / store, etc.</li>\n<li><strong>package</strong>: A file containing information such as version, dependencies, proxy, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Among these, the src folder, where most of the frontend work takes place, is examined in more detail below.</p>\n<h3 id=\"src-folder\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#src-folder\" aria-label=\"src folder permalink\" class=\"anchor-header before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>src Folder</h3>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/58f1a5274d570478c4b07c51d28182e4/0a47e/19-09-18-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 58.42105263157894%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/58f1a5274d570478c4b07c51d28182e4/15813/19-09-18-2.webp 190w,\n/static/58f1a5274d570478c4b07c51d28182e4/1cdb2/19-09-18-2.webp 380w,\n/static/58f1a5274d570478c4b07c51d28182e4/e88ff/19-09-18-2.webp 600w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/58f1a5274d570478c4b07c51d28182e4/a2d4f/19-09-18-2.png 190w,\n/static/58f1a5274d570478c4b07c51d28182e4/3f520/19-09-18-2.png 380w,\n/static/58f1a5274d570478c4b07c51d28182e4/0a47e/19-09-18-2.png 600w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/58f1a5274d570478c4b07c51d28182e4/0a47e/19-09-18-2.png\"\n            alt=\"img\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>components</strong>: The folder where component files are located</li>\n<li><strong>containers</strong>: The folder where container files are located, mainly containing code that maps state to props</li>\n<li><strong>pages</strong>: The folder where page files for routing are located</li>\n<li><strong>store</strong>: The folder for Redux operations, containing <strong>actions</strong> and <strong>reducers</strong> sub-folders</li>\n</ul>","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#react-project\">React Project</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#src-folder\">src Folder</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/frontend/19-09-18/","title":"Understanding React Project Structure","category":"FrontEnd","date":"2019-09-18"}}},"pageContext":{"postPath":"/frontend/19-09-18/","language":"eng","langRegex":"/contents/eng/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2145088972","256249292","63159454"],"slicesMap":{}}